Peru Stocks: Atacocha, Buenaventura, Candente, La Cima, Rio Alto

-- B y   A l e x   E m e r y
-- 
2011-06-27T20:55:18Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-27/peru-stocks-atacocha-buenaventura-candente-la-cima-rio-alto.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in  Peru  trading. Stock symbols are in parentheses
and share prices are as of 4:35 p.m.  New York  time.  The  Lima  General Index fell for a sixth session, losing 0.8
percent to 18,842.29. The MSCI All Peru Capped Index slid 0.8
percent to 2,435.75.  Mining stocks declined on investor concern over policies
that may be implemented by President-elect Ollanta Humala, who
takes office July 28, said SAB Inteligo analyst Daniel Mori.  Candente Copper Corp. (DNT)  , a Canadian mining
exploration company with operations in Peru, plunged 10 percent
to $1.14, a seven-month low. Cia. Minera Atacocha SA (ATACOBC1
PE), the Lima-based silver and zinc mining company, fell 4.6
percent to 1.03 soles.  Gold Fields La Cima SA (LACIMAC1 PE), a unit of Gold Fields
Ltd., dropped 3.7 percent to 3.95 soles as futures declined for
a third day in New York.  Rio Alto Mining Ltd. (RIO)  , a
Canadian gold exploration company, declined 2.4 percent to
$2.06. Cia. de Minas Buenaventura SAA (BVN PE), the countryâ€™s
biggest precious-metals miner, fell 1.9 percent to $36.50.  To contact the reporter on this story:
